<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=0 WIDTH="95%"><TR ><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#F0DCA0" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtextureL.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">DarkElfen</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">It kinda sucks BIGTIME. It would have been great if you could have used a teleporter to visit the places from before and see how the world has changed, to do some others quests (find better armor), slay tougher monsters (after all the black ring is at war with the other races now). <P>The ending is instead left totally open (apparently with a sequel in mind), but by making it so that months have passed it more feels like your inside a new game, one that works like: walk trough the desert, kill the demons, end.</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtexture.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Kroegie</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Totally agree, after the imps the game sucked bigtime,didn't enjoy the end, this is such a mistake of larian!The last place you visit is really boring with al those gargoyles and tiny area's.I really wanted to visit the elfs and dwarves again enjoying my reputation <IMG SRC="http://www.larian.com/ubb/smile.gif"> hope there comes a patch or something that will enable this.</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtextureL.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Phalanx</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Was thinking the same thing, it would be cool if DD could end a bit like Fallout2, where you had the option to continue playing, and notice the little changes that your victory brought. But then again, it isn't that easy to make this game like Fallout 2 towards the ending, the fact that you have that baby now... maybe the Larians could come up with some solution, I just hope that they are not going to act like Bluebyte did with their Settlers 4 game and SELL all the goodies of the game (random map generator, new race,...). But then again, DD is a very good game, and maybe there are still a few flaws, but try to understand that Divine Divinity is the first major title from Larian Studios and the game already got a pretty good name in the RPG community. I'd say that the Larians still have more then enough reasons to continue making patches and improvements for this game. The DD future looks brighter then ever  <IMG SRC="http://www.larian.com/ubb/smile.gif"> !</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtexture.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">DarkElfen</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Yeah, a patch would be great! Nothing fancy, just a teleporter back to the old world would be nice, with some extra enemies walking in the lands, especially in the orc camp (imps would do well there). They can make the story so that the orcs homeland has destroyed by the Black Circle and that the rest of the world isn't aware of this because the imps took over from the orcs.<P>As for the Fallout 2 thing, yeah that's kinda hard cos of the baby, but I believe the baby will be left in the care of the old wizard, cos what can the main char do with a demon baby? Raising the baby himself is kinda hard and weird.<p>[This message has been edited by DarkElfen (edited 25-09-2002).]</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtextureL.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Shiro</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I also agree the ending should change.. I think it's a nice open ending (story) but you should be able to go back to the old world (maybe a bit different) and be able to walk/talk around..<BR>At least let us hear "Congratulations" from SOMEBODY after we saved the WORLD  <IMG SRC="http://www.larian.com/ubb/biggrin.gif"> <BR>We should have been able to go back to Zandalor & Arhu en talked to them and go back to the world. I want my house back  <IMG SRC="http://www.larian.com/ubb/redface.gif"></FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtexture.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Phalanx</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">House back Shiro? I'd more call it a shack, Malcolm wasn't that rich, 2 bad we can't buy big estates like the ones Dante and Patrick have... would be cool to be one of the most important people in Verdistis... Or maybe your char can become duke (since you smashed Janus to pieces)?</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtextureL.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Shiro</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">What the fuck would WE do with such a big house..  <IMG SRC="http://www.larian.com/ubb/biggrin.gif"><BR>I only need my bed, a chest & maybe some barrels<BR>Would be cool though if the neighbours would drop by, and having a : welcome-in-the-neighbourhood-party..  <IMG SRC="http://www.larian.com/ubb/wink.gif"></FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtexture.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">DarkElfen</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Well a big house attracts thiefes and assasins, so that would be cool! You can set traps and such and one night you'll wake up cos a thief is trying to break in and triggered a trail bomb.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
